NT|In the middle of the hand, when you have the A and K and play the suit, you should play the K, as it makes it clearer you have the A. If you play the Ace, partner has no way of knowing if you have the K. In the old days, we used to lead K from AK on opening lead (instead of the modern way of leading the A), which made things less confusing. However, you lead A from AK only on opening lead, otherwise K from AK. If you had led the K, anne should signal with the 7, since she knows you must have the Ace (since she has the Q, you must have the A). Even when you lead the A, anne should signal the 7, because even if declarer had the K, it would be good for you to continue the suit, to knock out declarer's K and set up Anne's Q. However, had you started with the K, it would have been even more obvious. |
