hondo717: Now, let me discuss pam's comment. Many people play what is known as "coded 10s and 9s." That means, you lead the 10 or 9 from either the top of a sequence, or from a broken sequence. So you would lead the 10 from AJ10xx or KJ10xx (still lead the Q from QJ10xx.) You would also lead the 10 from 109xx and the J from J10x. When playing coded 10s, the 10, shows either a broken sequence or the top of nothing, whereas the J shows nothing higher. That is where the phrase "Jack denies" comes from. If you play coded 10s and 9s, the J absolutely denies any higher card.|
